The five noteworthy aspects of the Declaration of Independence are: 
1. It declared the Thirteen Colonies free from British rule; 
2. It outlined the inalienable rights of citizens; 
3. It offered a justification for the colonies' break from the British; 
4. It detailed the grievances against the King of England; and 
5. It declared independence from the British Empire on July 4, 1776.
